gomodel:SYNGO_4745  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: control for specificity of the novel AP1-γ2 (AP1G2) antiserum.\n\nFigure 4: knockout of AP1-σ1B (AP1S2) results in increased AP1-γ2 (AP1G2) in synaptosomal and synaptic Clathrin Coated Vesicle (CCV) biochemical fractions.\n\n\"We found γ2 to be present in CCV isolated from σ1B-/- as well as wt synapses, in line with the formation of AP-1/γ2 complexes.\"\n\nBecause it is unclear whether these synaptic CCVs are pre- or post-synaptic (or a mix of both), we generalize the annotation to \"synapse\".. Experimental description: \"The σ1B mouse ,knock-out' model has been described in Glyvuk et al., 2010\"\n\n\"Synaptosomes were lysed by 20 passages through a ball homogeniser (Isobiotec, Heidelberg, Ger) with a clearance of 12 μm. This extract was layered over 0-30% OptiPrep gradients, centrifuged at 65000g for 5 h and six fractions were collected. Protein concentration was determined according to the Bradford assay (BioRad, Munich, Ger). Synaptic CCV were isolated with a 20-50% sucrose gradient, centrifuged at 145,000 g over 1.5 h as described (Blondeau et al., 2004).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4745" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
